03/06/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- A group of 130 Greek businessmen led by Theodoros Karatzas, governor of the National Bank of Greece and chairman of the board of directors of the United Bulgarian Bank, kicked off a two-day visit to Bulgaria on Monday (2 June). The delegation will be exploring investment opportunities in the neighbouring country through a number of meetings with Bulgarian politicians, government members, leading businessmen and entrepreneurs. (Pari - 03/06/03; BTA - 30/05/03)
